UML:TaggedValue.value: The GeoSciML Collection package contains facade classes that facilitate the structuring of WFS response documents and other application uses.

The GeoSciML GeologicRelation package contains the root relation class.
Geologic Relations are typed, directed associations between geologic objects. Represents any of a wide variety of relationships that can exist between two or more Features or other entities. For example, the GeologicRelation "intrudes" is a relationship between an intrusive igneous rock and some host rock. Includes spatial, temporal, sequence, correlation, and parent/child relations.

A package of specialized data type elements for GeoSciML. These include geometric data types to describe orientation of geologic structures.
An specialized quantity range element, which extends SWECommon QuantityRange, is included to address the problem of the current inability to effectively query numbers encoded as a SWEComon RealPair using WFS/FES.
